I just sorta feel meh about it, While cookie is the same as it always was.

review_content:
ok, first off; this is a great pallet. It's huge, you get a ton of product in each pan and it's freaking adorable. However.. while I will be using some of these colors very frequently (OMG cookie! wow) some of the other colors were a bit darker than I expected (Dallas is darker/redder in person). I'm very fair toned and I think maybe they should have done 3 different pallets.. this one specifically would be perfection for someone in the mid-toned range, but having an option for a lighter and darker skinned person also would have made this a home run. Just my personal opinion. I still love it and will use it, I'm just hoping for something else similar in my shade range in the future.

product_name: Benefit Cosmetics Cheeks Stars Reunion Tour: Blush, Bronzer & Highlighter Palette
user_specs: ['Age 25-34', 'Eye Color Blue', 'Hair color Blonde', 'Skin Tone Light', 'Skin Type Dry']
review_color: Color: Dallas, Sugarbomb, Cookie, Georgia, Hoola
review_title: The one I've been waiting for!
review_content:
I waited and waited for the perfect cheek palette from Benefit to come out. this one was it for me. I am really glad I picked it up. These shades are smoothing and look wonderful mixed and solitary on the face. In the included picture I am wearing all the shades. Georgia, Dallas and sugarbomb do have a slight shimmer to them but it's more like a satin glow on the cheeks and it's very flattering and doesn't exaggerate texture. I like to use the shade Dallas as a bronzer topper on top of the hoola matte bronzer. Cookie is a gorgeous highlighter and really is blinding but can be sheared down a bit. I personally love it. i have also found that it doesn't emphasize my fine lines which i have on the tops of my cheeks from smiling. This is honestly a good deal for the big palette considering your getting full size products. All in all, a good buy and great to travel with as well.

review_title: Benefit has done it again! LOVE IT!
review_content:
Absolutely love. Blends perfectly. Shades are beautiful and that highlight is one of my (new) favorites! Missing a star because brush is a waste, bristles are too rough for application, I prefer a round buffer brush. They should just add another new shade, like another highlighter or hula lite and up the price a little bit so you get even more product to like 75$ (even though it’s already a killer deal!!!) just a thought!! The multi shade blush, is SO beautiful! Also the smell isn’t too strong, it’s enough to smell on the face, for the first few minutes after it’s applied but not too strong... personally I love the fruity smell of these palettes, especially this one! Because it’s more peachy, and so yummmmy! Way to go benefit, you killed this! My new go-to!!
